result.execSummary:
All charges against Christopher J Forncrook in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Christopher J Forncrook is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Extradition interstate agreement.

10:13 AM; Case called for Continued Extradition hearing. Prosecuting attorney Alyssa M Jay in court for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant Christopher J Forncrook in court, in custody.  Attorney Jeffrey W. Jensen Jr. in court for Christopher J Forncrook.  State notes their office has received a copy of the Interstate Compact which shows the defendant has waived extradition through that compact.  State also advises that Ohio is aware of this so they can pick the defendant up.  Based on all of this the State moves to dismiss this case.  No objection by Atty. Jensen.  Court will order case dismissed.
Extradition hearing on September 1, 2022 at 10:00 am.

8:58 AM; Case called for Extradition hearing.  Prosecuting attorney Alyssa M Jay in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Christopher J Forncrook in court, in custody.  Attorney Jeffrey W. Jensen Jr. in court for Christopher J Forncrook.  Atty. Jay is requesting a extension under 976.03(17) as the State is waiting for the Governor's warrant.  Atty. Jensen is asking the matter be dismissed and presents statements.  Atty. Jay responds.  Court will order both the State and Defense file a written report with the court before the end of the business day today with respect to the date the timeline for this case begins and their respective arguments on the request for extension and for dismissed.  Court will adjourn for continued extradition hearing tomorrow at 9:30.
Extradition hearing scheduled for September 2, 2022 at 09:30 am.
Extradition hearing on September 1, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Amended Warrant for Commitment signed by Judge Paul F Reilly August 15, 2022.

9:37 AM; Case called for Hearing. Prosecuting attorney Charles Patrick Hoffmann in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Christopher J Froncrook in court, in custody.  Attorney Jeffrey W. Jensen Jr. in court for Christopher J Froncrook.  Atty. Jensen first notes his client's last name is misspelled, it should be Forncrook, and the State has filed amended documents to that regard.  Court will make sure to make the appropriate correction to the defendant's last name.  Court inquires as to the status of the extradition.  Atty. Jensen advises his client is contesting extradition.  State asks the matter be set for contested hearing within the next 2 weeks. Atty. Jensen also asks to be heard on bail.  Atty. Jensen presents arguments and is asking for a signature bond.  State objects and presents statements.  For reasons placed on the record the Court will deny Atty. Jensen's request for bail.  Court will order defendant to continue to be held without bail pending conclusion of this matter.  Court adjourns for formal extradition hearing.
Extradition hearing scheduled for September 1, 2022 at 08:30 am.

02:09 PM Defendant Christopher J Froncrook in court, in custody.  Melissa J. Zilavy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State Public Defender Intern Patrick Sicula in court on behalf of the defendant.  Defendant is eligible for State Public Defender representation.  An attorney will be appointed.  Defense acknowledges receipt of complaint, affidavit, and warrant for commitment and waives reading.  Mr. Sicula indicates the defendant is contesting the extradition.  The Court is going to deny bail and will set this matter as soon as possible before the Judge for a contested extradition.  Hearing scheduled for August 15, 2022 at 09:00 am.
